{"questionId":"19770","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The <em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mi>H</mi></math></em> of a solution is given by the formula <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mi>H</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>−</mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mn>10</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mi>C</mi></math> where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi></math> is the hydrogen ion&nbsp;concentration in a solution, measured in moles per litre (<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mtext>Ml</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>).</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write an expression for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi></math> in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mi>H</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>−</mo><mi>p</mi><mi>H</mi></mrow></msup></math> &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>(M1)A1</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <strong>M1</strong> for an exponential equation with <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn></math> as the base.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>[2 marks]</strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"19770","referenceCode":"EXN.1.SL.TZ0.5b.i","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write an expression for C in terms of pH.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.1—Using standard form","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.5—Intro to logs"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}